codex
The exact failure is deterministic in both trusted runs: after the required full reload, the browser is back on the routed application screen but the test’s sign-out helper waits for the finance email text, which is not rendered. The two earlier screenshots exist; the checker screenshot is missing because execution never reaches that session.

Ranked hypotheses I’ll test:

1. The header’s account trigger uses a display name (or icon), not the email, so the locator is invalid after reload.
2. The header is collapsed/hidden at this viewport, requiring an accessible button locator.
3. Reload leaves auth data temporarily loading, so sign-out needs to wait on the authenticated shell.
4. The application route omits the normal header entirely.

The first predicts that an existing E2E sign-out helper or Header markup will expose a stable accessible account control that works without product changes.
